{
  "stem": "12904.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You know, after all, Pearl Harbor, they did start Pearl Harbor.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I had some really mixed feelings.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't believe we should be killing people any place, any time, actually.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I think we have a-- a right to defend ourselves.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I see.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Did news reports or personal accounts in any way dealing with the Holocaust filter through to where you were during or shortly after the war?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, when I found out that my aunt and uncle had been murdered, that-- we actually, we knew-- I don't think we knew, I knew or anyone else that I knew the extent of the concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was-- I don't think I was aware of that, to what extent and how many people had been murdered until later.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I knew that people could no longer get out, could no longer come into this country.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when I found out that the children's transport had been denied entrance to the United States-- that I found out early on-- I don't remember through what sources that became known.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There had been-- and the the ship, that was sent back.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I have a second cousin still living in Chicago whose parents were on that ship and were then murdered-- had to go back.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she had scrubbed floors in New York to earn enough money to get them, for the fare.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were supposed to go to Cuba, you know, the ship, and Cuba didn't want them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was all a-- a scam, you know, that they paid and this guy didn't have any authority or whatever to let them into Cuba.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So that I knew, I guess-- well, that was in '39, I believe.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
